---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="Atelier" description="Better Out Co. is a Cape Town company founded by Laura Weyel, bringing the first mould-free, lab-tested coffee enema to South Africa.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative" style="background-color:#EDF1E6;">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 pt-24 sm:pt-32 pb-16 sm:pb-24 text-center">
      <div class="label-wide text-matcha mb-10">
        A note from the founder
      </div>
      <h1 class="display text-cocoa leading-[1.02] text-[2.85rem] sm:text-7xl md:text-[6rem]">
        Better out<br/>
        <span class="display-italic text-sage">than in.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-12 lede max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Thirteen years, one quiet ritual — and the brand it became.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Body -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 prose-body text-espresso/90 pb-20">
    <p>
      Better Out Co. began the way most honest things do — quietly, in a kitchen, after years of trying everything else first. I had read the labels, swapped the pans, filtered the water, and fed my family in the way I had come to believe in. And yet there was one tool I kept returning to. One practice that genuinely changed how I felt: the coffee enema.
    </p>

    <p>
      My own story is why I trust it so completely. My liver doesn't make enough glutathione — the body's master antioxidant, the one that carries the daily load out. On paper, at twenty-seven, I should have been thriving. Instead I woke one morning in my rooftop apartment in Hong Kong wrung out after a full night's sleep. No energy. Thick brain fog. Something was wrong, and I knew it.
    </p>

    <p>
      Thousands of dollars of full-spectrum functional testing later, the results floored me. I ate organic. Grass-fed only. No seed oils. And still my body was carrying an enormous chemical load — microplastics, petroleum residues from nail polish, a long list of compounds from everyday household and cosmetic products. Things I was absorbing simply by living, breathing, eating.
    </p>

    <p>
      I refused a lifetime of medication just to help my liver keep up with what modern life pours into us. So I turned to coffee enemas — a gentle, daily way to support the liver and the body's own clearing. That was thirteen years ago. My energy has never been higher, my head never clearer. I feel more myself than I ever have.
    </p>

    <p>
      And I'm not alone in it. Over the years I've worked one-to-one with clients who came to me carrying that same heaviness — low energy, a foggy head, a body that felt like it was always running behind. Coffee enemas became part of how we turned that around. Not a quick fix, but a gentle, steadying ritual that supports the liver and lets the body do its own clearing of the load modern life piles on.
    </p>

    <p>
      What they tell me afterwards is remarkably consistent. That they feel lighter — in the body and in the head. The fog lifts. Energy holds steady through the afternoon instead of collapsing. Digestion settles. Sleep goes deeper. Skin looks like it's breathing again. Recovery comes faster when they've pushed themselves or been unwell. And more than any single thing, that quiet sense of coming home to themselves — of feeling clean, clear, and genuinely well from the inside out.
    </p>

    <div class="my-14 rounded-[22px] p-8 sm:p-11" style="background-color:#E3EFE6;">
      <p class="label-wide text-matcha mb-7 text-center">This is for you if …</p>
      <ul class="space-y-5">
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-sage select-none">—</span>
          <span>You do everything right — clean food, clean products, careful choices — and still wake up tired, foggy, and not quite yourself.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-sage select-none">—</span>
          <span>Your gut has never felt fully settled — the bloating, the sluggishness, that heavy, backed-up feeling that never quite shifts.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-sage select-none">—</span>
          <span>Your skin doesn't match how well you eat — dull, congested, breaking out, no matter how clean you live.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-sage select-none">—</span>
          <span>You already optimise everything — sleep, food, movement, supplements — and you're after the missing piece that takes you deeper.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="display-italic text-sage-deep text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-center mt-9">If any of that is you, this was made for you.</p>
    </div>

    <p>
      It's their experience, alongside my own, that convinced me this deserved to be made properly.
    </p>

    <p>
      Each time I went looking for it locally, I found the same problem. Mouldy coffee, vague sourcing, no testing, no one taking it seriously. The very thing meant to lighten the liver's load was, more often than not, adding to it.
    </p>

    <p>
      So I made the version I wished existed. Organic. Lab-tested. Guaranteed mould-free. Paired with a clean, well-made kit. The first of its kind in South Africa.
    </p>

    <div class="rule-centre my-16 text-espresso/35">
      <svg width="120" height="8" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#diamond-ornament"/></svg>
    </div>

    <blockquote class="pull-quote text-center my-12">
      The library is part of the work.
    </blockquote>

    <p>
      The free guides on this site are not a lead magnet — they are the worldview. Steady energy, real food, a lighter load, and healing at the root. The coffee enema is one chapter of that bigger story, and it tends to make the most sense once the rest is in place.
    </p>

    <p>
      Read what calls to you. Take one small thing at a time.
    </p>

    <div class="rule-centre my-16 text-espresso/35">
      <svg width="120" height="8" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#diamond-ornament"/></svg>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-12">
      <p class="font-serif italic font-light text-espresso/70 text-lg mb-2">With care,</p>
      <p class="display-italic text-clay-deep text-5xl leading-tight mb-4">Laura Weyel</p>
      <p class="label-wide text-espresso/55">Founder · Cape Town</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="border-t border-espresso/10" style="background-color:#E3EFE6;">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-10 py-24 text-center">
      <div class="rule-centre text-matcha/45 mb-8">
        <svg width="120" height="8" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#diamond-ornament"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h2 class="display text-3xl sm:text-5xl text-forest mb-7">Now <span class="text-matcha">available.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede max-w-xl mx-auto mb-10">
        Better Out Co. green coffee is in stores across Cape Town and ready to order — the easiest way is a quick message on WhatsApp.
      </p>
      <a href="https://wa.me/27630804439?text=Hi%20Laura%2C%20I%27d%20like%20to%20order%20Better%20Out%20Co.%20green%20coffee%20%F0%9F%8C%BF" rel="noopener" target="_blank" class="btn-espresso">
        Order on WhatsApp
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
